def: One who buffets; a boxer. Jonson.
Any vessel or canal in which blood circulates in an animal, asan artery or vein.
See in the Dictionary of Noted Names in Fiction.
A kind of halter usually made of raw hide.
A gutter; a stream, such as is usually dry in summer. [Prov.Eng. & Scot.]

Not felicitous; unhappy; unfortunate; not fortunate orappropriate in application; not well said, expressed, or done; as, aninfelicitous condition; an infelicitous remark; an infelicitousdescription; infelicitous words.
Tending to make peace; conciliatory.  Barrow.
One skilled in the knowledge of plants; a collector of, ordealer in, herbs, especially medicinal herbs.
The act or process of cutting out a portion of the iris inorder to form an artificial pupil.
